.TH "ELSERENO\-SCOPE" "5" "2026\-04\-19" "ElSereno scope file" "File formats"
.SH NAME
\f[B]scope.yaml\f[R] \(em authorised scope file for
\f[I]elsereno\f[R](1)
.SH DESCRIPTION
A \f[I]scope.yaml\f[R] file defines the authorised ranges, ports,
protocols, web binds, dialling blacklist, and optional canary for an
engagement.
.PP
A scope file is \f[B]optional\f[R] \(em when absent, ElSereno requires
an explicit acceptable\-use acknowledgement at every active command.
.SH FORMAT
.IP
.EX
version\f[B]:\f[R] 1
ranges\f[B]:\f[R]
  \f[B]\-\f[R] cidr\f[B]:\f[R] 192.168.0.0/16
    note\f[B]:\f[R] \(dqinternal lab\(dq
  \f[B]\-\f[R] cidr\f[B]:\f[R] 2001:db8::/32
    note\f[B]:\f[R] \(dqipv6 lab\(dq
ports\f[B]:\f[R]
  allow\f[B]:\f[R] \f[B][\f[R]502\f[B],\f[R] 102\f[B],\f[R] 44818\f[B],\f[R] 47808\f[B],\f[R] 2404\f[B],\f[R] 20000\f[B],\f[R] 1998\f[B],\f[R] 9999\f[B]]\f[R]
  deny\f[B]:\f[R] \f[B][]\f[R]
protocols\f[B]:\f[R]
  allow\f[B]:\f[R] \f[B][\f[R]modbus\f[B],\f[R] s7\f[B],\f[R] enip\f[B],\f[R] bacnet\f[B],\f[R] dnp3\f[B],\f[R] iec104\f[B],\f[R] xot\f[B],\f[R] atmodem\f[B],\f[R] banner\f[B]]\f[R]
  deny\f[B]:\f[R] \f[B][]\f[R]
binds\f[B]:\f[R]
  allow\f[B]:\f[R]
    \f[B]\-\f[R] 127.0.0.1:8787
    \f[B]\-\f[R] \(dq[::1]:8787\(dq
dial\f[B]:\f[R]
\f[I]  # In addition to the hardcoded ≤3\-digit block (always on).\f[R]
  blocked_numbers\f[B]:\f[R]
    \f[B]\-\f[R] \(dq+34112\(dq
    \f[B]\-\f[R] \(dq+34062\(dq
canary\f[B]:\f[R]
  enabled\f[B]:\f[R] false
  alert_webhook\f[B]:\f[R] \(dq\(dq
.EE
.SH SEMANTICS
.TP
\f[B]ranges\f[R]
CIDRs.
Both IPv4 and IPv6 are supported.
.TP
\f[B]ports.allow / ports.deny\f[R]
Deny wins over allow.
If \f[B]allow\f[R] is empty, all ports are allowed subject to
\f[B]deny\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]protocols.allow / protocols.deny\f[R]
Same precedence as ports.
.TP
\f[B]binds.allow\f[R]
Addresses the web server is allowed to bind to.
Non\-loopback binds additionally require \f[B]\(entls\-cert\f[R],
\f[B]\(entls\-key\f[R], and \f[B]\(eni\-know\-what\-im\-doing\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]dial.blocked_numbers\f[R]
Additional numbers blocked on offensive dialling.
≤3\-digit numbers are always blocked regardless.
.TP
\f[B]canary\f[R]
Optional webhook that fires when the canary condition is met (to be
defined per engagement).
